<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1955-09-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1955-09-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="161" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d161">
                        <head>161. Telegram 682 to Geneva<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d161fn1">Source: Department of State, Central Files, 611.93/9–355. Secret;
                                Priority. Drafted by Sebald; cleared by <persName corresp="#p_MRD_1">Murphy</persName>.</note></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1955-09-03">September 3, 1955, 6:46
                                    p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <pb facs="d161-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d161-1"/>
                        <p>682. For <persName corresp="#p_JUA_1">Johnson</persName>.</p>
                        <p>Reur 672. In light very cogent reasons set forth reftel we concur QTE
                            agreed announcement UNQTE should be released by you and <persName corresp="#p_WP_1">Wang</persName> accordance paragraph 6 Deptel
                            391.</p>
                        <pb facs="0257" n="210" type="typeset" xml:id="pg_210"/>
                        <p>We also concur tactics for Friday’s meeting suggested reftel but would
                            hope Dept could be informed immediately announcement made Geneva thus
                            enabling public relations aspect be taken care of in Washington and
                            possibly Denver almost simultaneously with Geneva announcement.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_HH_1"><hi rend="strong">Hoover</hi></persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>